---
title: Tilapia with Scallion Gochujang Pesto over Ginger Rice with Green Beans
description: Classic basil pesto never goes out of style, but tonight’s scallion pesto is the dynamic condiment we’ve been craving. Scallions are finely chopped, then mixed with sesame oil and seeds, ginger, sugar, lime juice, and gochujang. The tangy, sweet, savory, and spicy flavor explosion provides just the right contrast to mild tilapia fillets, fluffy ginger rice, and snappy green beans.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63208ad090d1f20dc80ece55-747bbfb7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f88441d6d437ce24b899e5.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tilapia-with-scallion-gochujang-pesto-64f88441d6d437ce24b899e5
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 59 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1180 mg
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce (except green beans). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and finely chop @scallions{4}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges.

> For 4 servings, halve one lime and quarter remaining.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add 1 TBSP ginger (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a medium #bowl{}, combine scallions, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, juice from half the lime, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, 1 tsp ginger, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and @gochujang sauce{1/2%ounce} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; add more ginger or lime juice to taste.

> For 4 servings, use all the sesame seeds, 2 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp ginger, and 2 tsp sugar.

Pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Tilapia is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

While tilapia cooks, pierce @green bean bag{} with a fork; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Transfer @green beans{6%ounce} to a second medium bowl; add @butter{1%tablespoon}. Stir until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice and green beans between plates. Arrange tilapia over rice; drizzle with scallion gochujang pesto and @soy sauce{2%tablespoon} to taste. Serve with lime wedges on the side.